# Archiving and Compressing Files (tar, gzip, bzip2)

tar – Archive Tool
tar is used to group multiple files into a single archive (usually with .tar extension).
Example: tar -cvf mybackup.tar Documents/
         tar -xvf archive_name.tar(extract)
         tar -tvf archive_name.tar(to list the files)

gzip – Compress a file
Compresses a file and adds .gz extension.
Example: gzip notes.txt  → becomes notes.txt.gz
         gunzip notes.txt.gz ( to decompress)

bzip2 – Better compression than gzip
Example: bzip2 report.log → becomes report.log.bz2
         bunzip2 report.log.bz2 (Decompress)


